    <h2 {...{
      "id": "packages---public-and-private-variables"
    }}>{`Packages - public and private variables`}</h2>
    <p>{`When it comes to declaring variables, to have them available to other files when the package is imported, declare the variable with a capital letter.`}</p>
    <p>{`Lowercase variables are private.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "variables"
    }}>{`Variables`}</h2>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-go"
      }}>{`// outside of func
var greeting = "hello"

func main() {
    // inside of func
    greeting := "Hello from Go"
    fmt.Println(test)
    fmt.Println(greeting)
